 <purpose>
<p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of conditions. Condition can be used to express if-statements consisting of operators and inputs (operands).
   </p>

 </purpose>

 <inscope>
   <li>
     Condition specified by a textual description;
   </li>
    <li>
     Use of external entities as input to a condition expression;
   </li>
   <li>
     Condition assignment;
   </li>
   <li>
     Condition relationships.
   </li>

   

 </inscope>
 <outscope>
